pgTitle: List of RAF aircrew in the Battle of Britain (A–C)

rows.text: Born Ludlow, Shropshire, 25 June 1917. Commissioned Nov 1940; retired as Wing Commander June 1964; died 1977.
||KIA 30 September 1940 Spitfire crashed on Alnmouth Beach due to a flying accident.
||KIA 2 September 1940; Hurricane P3067 shot down in combat over the Thames Estuary. (Pilot)
||MIA 26 August 1940 Defiant L6985 destroyed a Do 17 then was shot down by Bf 109s over Thanet, crashed into Herne Bay, Banham the pilot baled out and was rescued, Baker missing.
||MIA 8 August 1940 Hurricane P3381 shot down over the channel and crashed into the sea, Baker missing.
||Born Worksop, Notts., 19 May 1920; Released from RAF as Squadron Leader, Jan 1946
||KIA 11 August 1940 (possibly "friendly fire") (Pilot) Hurricane N2667 shot down possibly by a Spitfire and crashed into the sea, Baker baled out but died in the sea.
|| Defiant L6985 destroyed a Do 17 then was shot down by Bf 109s over Thanet, crashed into Herne Bay, Banham baled out and was rescued but air gunner Baker was missing.
||KIA 28 September 1940 (pilot) Hurricane V6776 damaged by Bf109s over Fareham, Bann baled out but was killed when parachute failed.
||In September 1939 CO of 113 Fighter Escadrille, which defended Warsaw. Died 8 August 1970 in UK.
||KIA 4 September 1940 Spitfire R6909 possibly shot down by a Do 17 off Bognor, Barker baled out but was killed.
||KIA 11 July 1940 (Pilot) Spitfire L1069 damaged in combat with Bf109s off Portland, Barran bailed out and was rescued from the sea but died before reaching land.
||KIA 7 October 1940 ¶ † (Pilot) Hurricane V6800 shot down in combat by a Bf 109 over Wrotham, crashed at Darenth.
|| Ace, 12 aircraft destroyed, Died 18th April 2001||| Died 2001
Born Kamloops, British Columbia, Canada, 7 June 1916. Retired Feb 1959 as Wing Commander; died 2 September 2010
Batchelor, Gordon Herbert Surname also spelt "Batcheloe" - CWGC website
||KIA 10 October 1940 (Pilot) Hurricane V7537 crashed at Cooling Marsh during a routine patrol, thought to be due to oxygen failure.
Commissioned June 1941; retired Aug 1970; died October 2003.
MIA 23 September 1940 †(Pilot) Spitfire R7016 failed to return from operational sortie over the Channel, Beaumont missing.
||KIFA 7 October 1940 (Pilot) Hurricane N2707 destroyed on landing due to engine failure.
||KIA 12 August 1940 Hurricane P3304 shot down in combat with Bf 109s off Ramsgate, crashed into the sea and Beley was rescued but died of wounds.

Born Burslem, Staffordshire, 13 March 1913. Cannon shell exploded in cockpit, 1 October 1940, blinding him in one eye and wounding his right arm and leg; baled out and hospitalised; underwent plastic surgery at Queen Victoria Hospital, East Grinstead, by facial reconstruction pioneer Dr. Archie McIndoe; became one of the founding members of McIndoe's "Guinea Pigs"; died 30 January 2004
||KIA 28 August 1940 (Pilot) Spitfire N3105 crashed in flames at Tenterden after combat with Bf 109s.
||KIA 7 September 1940 Hurricane P2962 failed to return after combat ober the Thames Estuary. Suspected crash site and remains found post war but not positively identified.
||MIA 7 September 1940(Pilot) Hurricane P3049 shot down in combat over the Thames Estuary and crashed as Sheppey.
||KIFA 22 July 1940 (during aerobatics) † (Pilot) Hurricane P3895 crashed prior to landing at Caste Camps aerodrome.
||KIFA 13 July 1940 (Pilot) Spitfire R6688 stalled during dogfight training and crashed and burned at Balsham.
CBE, DSO*, DFC*, DFC(Netherlands), MoM1 (Czech), AFC*
||WIA 29 October 1940; Died 9 November 1940 †(Pilot) Hurricane shot down in combat with Bf 109s and crashed and burned near Ashford, Black badly wounded and died 9 November 1940.
||KIA 29 October 1940 (Pilot) Believed attacked by a Bf 109 in his Spitfire P7423 during a patrol over London and crashed at Chelmsford.
||KIA 18 August 1940 (Pilot) Hurricane P3208 crashed following attack by a JG26 pilot.

MIA 3 May 1943, (Wg Cdr) shot down in combat over Netherlands; aged 31; Born Edmonton, Alberta, Canada, 25 February 1912; son of Kenneth A. and Grace L. Blatchford, of Edmonton, Alberta, Canada; remembered on Panel 118 of the Runnymede Memorial. Shared 41 Squadron's first World War II victory, a He 111, with Sgts. E. A. Shipman & A. Harris on 17 October 1939;

||MIA 16 November 1940 (216 Sqn) when aircraft ran out of fuel at sea between HMS Argus and Malta; aged 20; Born London, 8 November 1919; son of Air Cdr. John A. Boret, CBE, MC, AFC, who commanded 41 Squadron from May 1933-Mar 1937; remembered on Panel 7 of the Runnymede Memorial.
||KIFA 18 October 1940 (Pilot) Hurricane P3930 crashed and burned at Kempton Park race course in bad weather returning from a patrol.
||KIA 1 October 1940 (Pilot) Hurricane P2900 shot down in combat with Bf 110ss over the Isle of Wight, Bowen missing.
||KIA 28 September 1940, aged 26. Born Casselman, Ontario, Canada, 27 March 1914 (Pilot)
Surviving aircrew Born Edinburgh, Scotland, 1919. Commission terminated on completion of service, 12 April 1941
||KIA 1 October 1940 Hurricane V6686 shot down in combat with Bf 109s over the Isle of Wight.
Died, in rank of Colonel, 13 February 1946 in crash of Douglas DC-3 Dakota in Orpington near London.
Died 26 August 2007 in Spring, Texas, USA
||POW 20 October 1940; Blenheim P6952 shot down attacking enemy aircraft off Norwegian coast; Flt Lt G M Baird captured, Burton captured wounded, Sgt R Copcutt missing, W/O S V Wood captured wounded.
KIFA 30 November 1948 in Ruahines, during photographic reconnaissance in Gisborne area of NZ. Born Wellington, New Zealand, 7 February 1918.

||POW 13 September 1940; Blenheim Z5721 crashed in Channel off Calais during night patrol (circumstances unknown); Flt Lt Ker-Ramsay, W/O George Dixon and Byrne baled out and were captured. KIA 24 July 1943 (Pilot)
